14/03/2025
1. GPT recommands me to start with Frontend, still watching the tutorial videos about react.
2. install and deploy both front end and back end first.
3. In backend:
(1)rooms.json stores the condition of the room (availabe or occupied); 
(2)srver.js is for the logic of backend(read from room.json, change the condition and update the room condition)

4. In frontend:
(1)RoomCard.jsx is the condition of room (green or red) and buttons
(2)App.jsx is manage the condition of rooms and manage data
(3)main.jsx is the entrance of React, deliver these things to webpage

It seems like React can fullfil all functions now why we still need backend? cuz now we are using backend as a DB to store data, if the user refresh, it wont lost






